quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  41,26,"Those who disbelieve say, “Do not listen to this Qur’an, but make noise [when it is recited], so that you may prevail.”"
  41,27,"We will surely make those who disbelieve taste a severe punishment, and We will surely recompense them according to the worst of what they used to do"
  41,28,"Such is the recompense of the enemies of Allah: the Fire, which will be their eternal home, as a recompense for their rejection of Our verses"
  41,29,"Those who disbelieved will say, “Our Lord, show us those jinn and men who led us astray; we will trample them under our feet, so that they become among the lowest.”"
  41,30,"Those who say, “Our Lord is Allah,” then remain steadfast, the angels will descend upon them [at the time of death, saying], “Do not fear, nor grieve, but receive glad tidings of Paradise which you were promised"
  41,31,"We are your allies in the life of this world and in the Hereafter. You will have therein whatever your souls desire, and you will have therein whatever you ask for"
  41,32,"a hospitality from the All-Forgiving, the Most Merciful One.”"